There currently exist low-cost solutions for CAD file modification and rapid prototyping;
a hobbyist can build a 3D printer for about $500, and there are numerous free options
for CAD software thanks to the open source movement. However, current digitization
solutions cost thousands of dollars, creating a barrier to many engineers. We seek to
build a low-cost machine capable of filling this void.
